parameters.name: filters
parameters.description: Optional filters to limit results. You can use status. (dict) --- Information about a filter. name (string) --- The name of the filter. values (list) --- A list of values. (string) ---

nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the world.

nested_items.name: createdAt
nested_items.description: The time, in milliseconds since the epoch, when the world was created.

nested_items.name: generationJob
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (arn) of the world generation job.

nested_items.name: template
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (arn) of the world template.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: If the previous paginated request did not return all of the remaining results, the response object's nextToken parameter value is set to a token. To retrieve the next set of results, call ListWorlds again and assign that token to the request object's nextToken parameter. If there are no remaining results, the previous response object's NextToken parameter is set to null.
